name: Exeggcute
flavorText: Even though it appears to be eggs of some sort, it was discovered to be a life-form more like plant seeds.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Exeggutor
flavorText: It is called "The Walking Jungle." If a head grows too big, it falls off and becomes an Exeggcute.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage times the number of Colorless Pokemon your opponent has in play.

name: Wurmple
flavorText: It lives among the tall grass and in forests. It repels attacks by raising up the spikes on its rear.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for Wurmple and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Silcoon
flavorText: It drinks dew that collects on its silk and waits for evolution. Its hard cocoon repels attacks.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Beautifly
flavorText: It has an aggressive nature. It stabs prey with its long, narrow mouth to drain the prey's fluids.
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from your opponent's Pokemon-EX.
Attack1Text: You may have your opponent switch his or her Active Pokemon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon.

name: Cascoon
flavorText: It never forgets any attack it endured while in the cocoon. After evolution, it seeks payback.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks during your opponent's next turn.

name: Dustox
flavorText: It violently flutters its wings to scatter toxic dust when attacked. It becomes active after sunset.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep and Poisoned.

name: Dustox
flavorText: It violently flutters its wings to scatter toxic dust when attacked. It becomes active after sunset.
Attack2Text: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Nincada
flavorText: It can sometimes live underground for more than 10 years. It absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon does 10 damage to itself.

name: Ninjask
flavorText: Because it moves so quickly, it sometimes becomes unseeable. It congregates around tree sap.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokemon is your Active Pokemon, you may discard a card from your hand. If you do, discard the top card of your opponent's deck.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Ninjask and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Shedinja
flavorText: A most peculiar Pokemon that somehow appears in a Poke Ball when a Nincada evolves.
Attack1Text: Put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Pokemon. Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 50 damage times the number of damage counters on this Pokemon.

name: Tropius
flavorText: The bunch of fruit around its neck ripens twice a year and is delicious. It's a highly favored tropical snack.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Victini
flavorText: When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being's entire body will be overflowing with power.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Fletchinder
flavorText: The hotter the flame sac on its belly, the faster it can fly, but it takes some time to get the fire going.
Attack1Text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokemon Tool cards attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Talonflame
flavorText: When attacking prey, it can reach speeds of up to 310 mph. It finishes its prey off with a colossal kick.
Attack1Text: Draw 3 cards. You may switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon does 20 damage to itself.

name: Articuno
flavorText: A legendary bird Pokemon that is said to appear to doomed people who are lost in icy mountains.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 Water Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Articuno
flavorText: A legendary bird Pokemon that is said to appear to doomed people who are lost in icy mountains.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 40 more damage for each heads.

name: Wingull
flavorText: It makes its nest on steep sea cliffs. Riding updrafts, it soars to great heights.

name: Pelipper
flavorText: It is a messenger of the skies, carrying small Pokemon and eggs to safety in its bill.
Attack1Text: Heal from this Pokemon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: It raises its tail to check its surroundings. The tail is sometimes struck by lightning in this pose.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokemon can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Voltorb
flavorText: Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a Poke Ball, it has zapped many people.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon does 60 damage to itself.

name: Electrode
flavorText: It stores an overflowing amount of electric energy inside its body. Even a small shock makes it explode.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.
Attack2Text: You may move all Energy from this Pokemon to your Benched Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Zapdos
flavorText: A legendary Pokemon that is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.
Attack2Text: This attack does 40 damage to 1 of your Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Electrike
flavorText: It stores static electricity in its fur for discharging. It gives off sparks if a storm approaches.

name: Manectric
flavorText: It discharges electricity from its mane. It creates a thundercloud overhead to drop lightning bolts.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Thundurus-EX
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage. If tails, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon does 50 damage to itself.

name: Natu
flavorText: It usually forages for food on the ground but may, on rare occasions, hop onto branches to peck at shoots.

name: Natu
flavorText: It usually forages for food on the ground but may, on rare occasions, hop onto branches to peck at shoots.

name: Xatu
flavorText: They say that it stays still and quiet because it is seeing both the past and future at the same time.

Attack2Text: Your opponent reveals his or her hand. Discard a Trainer card you find there.

name: Shuppet
flavorText: It loves vengeful emotions and hangs in rows under the eaves of houses where vengeful people live.
Attack1Text: Discard a Special Energy attached to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon.

name: Banette
flavorText: Strong feelings of hatred turned a puppet into a Pokemon. If it opens its mouth, its cursed energy escapes.
Ability1Text: Each Pokemon Tool card in play has no effect.

name: Banette
flavorText: Strong feelings of hatred turned a puppet into a Pokemon. If it opens its mouth, its cursed energy escapes.

Attack2Text: Put 5 damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Deoxys
flavorText: DNA from a space virus mutated and became a Pokemon. It appears where auroras are seen.
Attack1Text: If you go first, you can use this attack on your first turn. Draw 2 cards.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon's Overdrive Smash attack does 60 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Gallade-EX
Attack1Text: You may have your opponent switch his or her Active Pokemon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your remaining Prize cards.

name: M Gallade-EX
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon that has any damage counters on it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Gligar
flavorText: It flies straight at its target's face then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed and Poisoned.

name: Gliscor
flavorText: Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its preyâ€¦ Then its elongated fangs do the rest.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Binacle
flavorText: Two Binacle live together on one rock. When they fight, one of them will move to a different rock.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokemon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.

name: Hawlucha
flavorText: Although its body is small, its proficient fighting skills enable it to keep up with big bruisers like Machamp and Hariyama.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 40 more damage.

name: Absol
flavorText: It appears when it senses an impending natural disaster. As a result, it was mistaken as a doom bringer.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand onto your Bench, you may move 3 damage counters from 1 of your opponent's Pokemon to another of his or her Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Inkay
flavorText: It flashes the light-emitting spots on its body, which drains its opponent's will to fight. It takes the opportunity to scuttle away and hide.
Attack1Text: Choose a random card from your opponent's hand. Your opponent reveals that card and shuffles it into his or her deck.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Jirachi
flavorText: It is said to have the ability to grant any wish for just one week every thousand years.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 7 cards of your deck and put 1 of them into your hand. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.
Attack2Text: Discard all Energy attached to this Pokemon. The Defending Pokemon is Knocked Out at the end of your opponent's next turn.

name: Togepi
flavorText: A proverb claims that happiness will come to anyone who can make a sleeping Togepi stand up.
Attack1Text: Your opponent draws a card.

name: Togetic
flavorText: They say that it will appear before kindhearted, caring people and shower them with happiness.
Attack1Text: Shuffle 3 basic Energy cards from your discard pile into your deck.

name: Togekiss
flavorText: It shares many blessings with people who respect one another's rights and avoid needless strife.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin for each Energy attached to this Pokemon. This attack does 50 damage times the number of heads.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Togekiss
flavorText: It shares many blessings with people who respect one another's rights and avoid needless strife.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon, you may look at the top 8 cards of your deck. Choose any basic Energy cards you find there and attach them to your Pokemon in any way you like. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

name: Dragonair
flavorText: A mystical Pokemon that exudes a gentle aura. It is said to have the ability to change the weather.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 60 damage times the number of heads.

name: Dragonite
flavorText: It is said to make its home somewhere in the sea. It guides crews of shipwrecks to shore.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon, you may heal all damage from 1 of your Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Dragonite

Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokemon is your Active Pokemon, you may attach a Fire Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Dragon Pokemon.
